    <p>This is the section every customer asks about. Read it carefully.</p>

    <h3>Content you give us</h3>
    <p>The brand voice samples, existing blog posts, customer logs, product docs, target keywords, and any other input you upload or paste into the platform stay yours. You give us a limited license to use that material to operate the product for you — write articles, build internal linking, suggest keywords, train your brand-voice model. We do not use your material to train a public model or share it with any other customer.</p>

    <h3>Content theStacc generates</h3>
    <p>Articles, GBP posts, social posts, meta descriptions, schema markup, and any other text or image the platform produces for you ("generated content") are owned by theStacc the moment they are created. The moment a piece of generated content is approved and published to your site or your channel, theStacc grants you a perpetual, worldwide, royalty-free, transferable license to use, edit, republish, syndicate, translate, monetize, and sub-license that piece of content for any purpose. The license survives cancellation of your subscription.</p>
    <p>In plain English: theStacc owns the underlying IP, but once a piece of content is approved and goes live, you can do whatever you want with it forever. You can keep it on your site, republish it, edit it, syndicate it to other publishers, sell the rights to someone else. Cancelling your subscription does not retroactively pull a license — every article that went live during your subscription stays yours to use.</p>
    <p>If your business is acquired, the license follows the business. If you sell the article rights to a third party, the license follows the rights.</p>

    <h3>Why we structure it this way</h3>
    <p>Most AI content platforms claim joint or unclear ownership. We split it cleanly: theStacc owns the underlying IP so we can defend it against copycats and infringement, you get a perpetual license so the content is permanently safe to use. The license terms are written so a court reading them will land on the side of you, the customer.</p>
